Javascript Default Input
by Jake Wendt, 2007




Demo
====

http://github.jakewendt.com/javascript_default_input/


Usage
=====


Options
=======

class: default
	To allow input text fields to be used without labels.
	The field shows the "id" until the user has changed it.
	(will use the value of the input tag with the same id followed 
	by "_default" as its default over its id)
class: password
	Converts the field to a "password" once the user has entered one.
	Converts the field back to a "text" if empty.


Example
=======

<input id='user_name'     class='default'          type='text'/>
<input id='user_name_default' type='hidden' value="Enter your user name" />

<input id='user_password' class='default password' type='password'/>
<input id='user_password_default' type='hidden' value="and password" />

